===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|knight}}, {{m|enm|knyght}}, {{m|enm|kniht}}, from {{inh|en|ang|cniht||boy, servant}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kneht}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|en|knyght}}

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|historical}} A young servant or follower; a trained military attendant in service of a [[lord]].
# {{lb|en|historical}} A minor nobleman with an honourable military rank who had served as a [[page]] and [[squire]].
# {{lb|en|by extension}} An armored and mounted [[warrior]] of the [[Middle Ages]].
#: ''King Arthur and the '''Knights''' of the Round Table''
# {{lb|en|modern}} A person on whom a [[knighthood]] has been conferred by a [[monarch]].
# {{lb|en|literary}} A brave, chivalrous and honorable man devoted to a noble cause or [[love interest]].
# {{lb|en|chess}} A [[chess piece]], often in the shape of a [[horse]]'s head, that is moved two squares in one direction and one at right angles to that direction in a single move, leaping over any intervening pieces.
# {{lb|en|card games|dated}} A playing card bearing the figure of a knight; the knave or jack.
# {{lb|en|entomology}} Any of various [[nymphalid]] butterflies of the genus {{taxlink|Ypthima|genus|ver=190708}}.
# {{lb|en|modern}} A generic name for various [[mushroom]]s belonging to the [[order]] [[Agaricales]], the {{vern|gilled mushroom}}s; scientific name ''[[Tricholoma]]''.

